==English==

===Etymology===
German, from [[ur-]] + [[Sprache]] ‘speech’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'ʊəsprɑ:kə/, ''foreign'' /'u:rʃpra:xə/
oosh-pah-kah

===Noun===
{{en-noun|Ursprache|Ursprachen}}

# a [[proto-language]]; a [[language]] only spoken by [[linguist]]s; a language with no native speakers; nonsense, gibberish
#:*'''1993''', I had lost him.  He might have been speaking '''Ursprache''', for all that I understood. — Will Self, ''My Idea of Fun''

===Usage notes===
Ursprache was the winning word at the 2006 [[:Wikipedia:Scripps National Spelling Bee|Scripps National Spelling Bee]].